                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A text on erotology with numerous coloured illustrations. The first four positions are
                            attached with āsans. Then there are images that describe the text above
                            and below the cartouche titled ‘JALSE’ but they are under a larger
                            classificatory umbrella of ‘shakal’. Then with chapter 18 the narrative
                            change to Ḥikāyat or stories with accompanying images. There are
                            chapters on aphrodisiacs and medicines too. </summary>
